<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="266" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,433,638]" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,469,494]" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species needs to be re-studied based on 
<typeStatus box="[891,939,470,494]" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">type</typeStatus>
material because its identity is not well established. It may be a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Ribaut)" authorityName="Ribaut" box="[576,784,505,530]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macrosteles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="266" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevis">
<emphasis box="[576,599,506,529]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[616,681,505,529]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">laevis</emphasis>
(Ribaut)
</taxonomicName>
based on the length of the aedeagal processes which are longer than in the other species from 
<collectingCountry box="[567,666,541,566]" name="Pakistan" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
. However, although the original drawings of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ahmed" authorityYear="1986" box="[1170,1290,541,565]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macrosteles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="266" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shahidi">
<emphasis box="[1170,1193,542,565]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1207,1290,541,565]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">shahidi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are poor, the aedeagal shaft is shown as much shorter than in 
<taxonomicName box="[722,828,577,601]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macrosteles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="266" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevis">
<emphasis box="[722,745,578,601]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[763,828,577,601]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">laevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<typeStatus box="[846,902,578,602]" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">Type</typeStatus>
specimens and data were not specified in the original description. Although the 
<typeStatus box="[537,585,614,638]" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">type</typeStatus>
depository was probably 
<collectionCode box="[875,960,614,637]" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">ZMUK</collectionCode>
, no 
<typeStatus box="[1006,1054,614,638]" pageId="9" pageNumber="266">type</typeStatus>
specimen could be found there.
</paragraph>
